race.comment: STAR COMPASS (11) has placed 4/4 and third up is ready to break through. Placed at Murtoa 26 days ago and three winners have come out of that. Races forward and will get every chance. BIG ROOSTER (2) just missed at Hamilton on debut and it was a decent effort after a slow away. Will present fitter and should be hitting the line hard. Maher-trained LADY LONSDALE (12) resumed at Sandown-Hillside 36 days ago well in the market but didn't finish it off. Brought promising form to that and has been kept up to the mark with a Cranbourne jumpout. Draws wide but has a key gear switch and on song she's right up to this. FLYING DONE (8) resumes for a local stable and has jumped out twice with race rider Yendall aboard. His only start was in the rich Gold Elvstroem Classic at Swan Hill when he was slow away. Has to be kept safe.
